(Detailed Explanation) Tj
T*
(What This Topic Means) Tj
T*
(Figures of speech create imagery, emphasis, and style in language. In English, students) Tj
T*
(do better when they understand not only the definition of Figures of Speech, but also) Tj
T*
(the language, symbols, and patterns that appear whenever this topic is tested.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Core Explanation) Tj
T*
(The central focus in Figures of Speech is metaphor, simile, personification, hyperbole,) Tj
T*
(and effect. A strong explanation should show the idea clearly, connect it to prior) Tj
T*
(knowledge, and then walk through the method students are expected to use whenever they) Tj
T*
(meet this topic in classwork or examination questions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Understanding) Tj
T*
(A good classroom illustration for Figures of Speech is explaining the effect of a) Tj
T*
(metaphor in a sentence. When students can talk through that kind of example slowly and) Tj
T*
(correctly, they usually find it much easier to transfer the same reasoning to new) Tj
T*
(questions.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why Students Find It Difficult) Tj
T*
(One frequent problem in Figures of Speech is spotting a figure of speech without) Tj
T*
(describing its effect. Students also struggle when they try to memorize final answers) Tj
T*
(without understanding the steps that make the answer valid. Clear explanations, careful) Tj
T*
(checking, and repeated guided practice reduce this difficulty.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Real Learning Application) Tj
T*
