(In real study situations, students master Figures of Speech by practising with tasks) Tj
T*
(that mirror identification and interpretation. The topic becomes more meaningful when it) Tj
T*
(is linked to examples, revision drills, and exam-style questions that reflect how) Tj
T*
(English is assessed.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on explaining the effect of a metaphor in a sentence.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in metaphor, simile, personification, hyperbole, and effect) Tj
T*
(that the question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Figures of Speech step by step without skipping) Tj
T*
(reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on identification and interpretation.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid spotting a figure of speech without describing its effect) Tj
T*
(while solving it.) Tj
T*
(4. Review the result and connect it back to the topic overview.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Common Mistakes) Tj
T*
(- Misunderstanding the core focus of Figures of Speech: metaphor, simile,) Tj
T*
(personification, hyperbole, and effect.) Tj
T*
(- Spotting a figure of speech without describing its effect.) Tj
T*
(- Jumping to an answer without showing the steps or reasoning clearly.) Tj
T*
(- Practising Figures of Speech without checking whether the method matches the question) Tj
T*
(being asked.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Study Tips) Tj
T*
(- Rewrite the overview of Figures of Speech in your own words after studying it.) Tj
T*
(- Use short exercises built around identification and interpretation before trying) Tj
T*
(harder tasks.) Tj
T*
(- Keep track of mistakes such as spotting a figure of speech without describing its) Tj
T*
(effect and write the correction beside each one.) Tj
T*
(- Revise Figures of Speech regularly so the method behind metaphor, simile,) Tj
T*
(personification, hyperbole, and effect becomes familiar.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Practice Exercises) Tj
T*
(- Explain the overview of Figures of Speech and describe how it fits into English.) Tj
T*
(- Work through an example based on explaining the effect of a metaphor in a sentence and) Tj
T*
(explain each step.) Tj
T*
